column2: Jeg opfordrer Dem til stående at iagttage et minuts stilhed.
column3: Please rise, then, for this minute' s silence.

column2: De har udtrykt ønske om en debat om dette emne i løbet af mødeperioden.
column3: You have requested a debate on this subject in the course of the next few days, during this part-session.
(The House rose and observed a minute' s silence)

column2: Gennem pressen og tv vil De være bekendt med en række bombeeksplosioner og drab i Sri Lanka.
column3: You will be aware from the press and television that there have been a number of bomb explosions and killings in Sri Lanka.

column2: Fru formand, en bemærkning til forretningsordenen.
column3: Madam President, on a point of order.

column2: En af de personer, der blev myrdet for ganske nylig i Sri Lanka, var hr. Kumar Ponnambalam, der besøgte Europa-Parlamentet for få måneder siden.
column3: One of the people assassinated very recently in Sri Lanka was Mr Kumar Ponnambalam, who had visited the European Parliament just a few months ago.

column2: Som De kan se, indfandt det store "år 2000-problem" sig ikke. Til gengæld har borgerne i en del af medlemslandene været ramt af meget forfærdelige naturkatastrofer.
column3: Although, as you will have seen, the dreaded 'millennium bug' failed to materialise, still the people in a number of countries suffered a series of natural disasters that truly were dreadful.

column2: Jeg erklærer Europa-Parlamentets session, der blev afbrudt fredag den 17. december, for genoptaget. Endnu en gang vil jeg ønske Dem godt nytår, og jeg håber, De har haft en god ferie.
column3: I declare resumed the session of the European Parliament adjourned on Friday 17 December 1999, and I would like once again to wish you a happy new year in the hope that you enjoyed a pleasant festive period.

column2: I mellemtiden ønsker jeg - som også en del kolleger har anmodet om - at vi iagttager et minuts stilhed til minde om ofrene for bl.a. stormene i de medlemslande, der blev ramt.
column3: In the meantime, I should like to observe a minute' s silence, as a number of Members have requested, on behalf of all the victims concerned, particularly those of the terrible storms, in the various countries of the European Union.
